Porter College House A was originally constructed in 1970 as a four-story cast-in-place reinforced concrete building. It underwent a major renovation in 2009-10 involving the addition of two additional floors, seismic and structural upgrades and major maintenance. The building is C-shaped with its long axis oriented north-south. The west side frames a portion of the interior courtyard of Porter College and faces Porter House B. The east side is flanked by a landscaped area and then the college access road.  Porter College House A was certified LEED-NC GOLD in 2012.
Porter College Residence B Seismic Corrections and Renovations project 978750 completed in 2009.  LEED-NC Silver certified 2010.
Porter College Dining Common was certified LEED-CI SILVER in 2011.
